<h2>MadLib Form</h2>

<form action="./madlib" method="get">
	<label for="id_name">What is your first name?</label>
	<input type="text" id="id_name" name="f_name" placeholder="Your Name"><br>

	<label for="id_city">Where were you born?</label>
	<input type="text" id="id_city" name="f_birthplace" placeholder="someplace cool"><br>
	
	<label for="id_friend">Who is your best friend?</label>
	<input type="text" id="id_friend" name+"f_friend" placeholder="Joe"><br>
	
	<label for="id_food">What is your favorite food?</label>
	<input type="text" id="id_food" name+"f_food" placeholder="Potatoes"><br><br>
	
	<label for="animals">Choose an animal:</label>

    <select name="animalz" id="animals">
        <option value="dog">Dog</option>
        <option value="cat">Cat</option>
        <option value="amogus">Amogus</option>
        <option value="wamogus">Wide Amogus</option>
    </select>
	
	<button type="submit" value="Submit">Submit</button>
</form> 

<ul>
	<li>the "action" attribute of the form is the destination of the form</li>
	<li>the "method" attribute of the form specifies how key/value pairs will be sent to the server. GET sends parameters in the url. POST is a more secure transmission of info.</li>
	<li>the "for" attribute of a label must match the id of its associated input</li>
	<li>the "name" attribute of a becomes the key of the key-value pair sent to the server</li>
	<li>it's preferential to use a button (tag) of type=submit instead of a submit (tag), as submit tags are not stylable</li>
</ul>

